<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1006" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                    <head>Grutli Union of Travers</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Travers</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 15, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: The Neuenburg, Boudry, Travers, Couvet,
                        Fleurier, and Chaux-de-Fond sections of the Swiss Grutli Union, in their
                        meetings of yesterday, unanimously resolved to approve of the address of
                        sympathy and condolence to the American Union.</p>
                    <p>The undersigned, as secretary, has the honor to enclose you the resolution,
                        and subscribe himself your obedient servant,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>J. STEFFEN, </signed>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundesrath</hi>, <hi rend="italic">in
                            Berne</hi>.</p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>